  <span id="freeText1503721396339700083" style="display:none">This little book is a gem for writers, writer wannabes (like me) and lovers of Southern Fiction and the deep south (Jackson, MS!). Eudora Welty's autobiographical storytelling seemed effortless, and it flowed more interestingly than a lot of novels I've read. I loved how she examined little puzzle pieces (poignant vignettes from her growing up years and family history) and put them together to reveal the big picture of her life's work--her fully realized passion for writing. I envy her perspective -- looking back from greatness to the mundane that made her great.</span>
